# still significant

The mapping efficiency depends on the genotype of the wasp and on the tissue. However, the effects are very small (if we exclude heads from Lb84):

summary(stats$overall_rate)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   85.67   95.63   95.96   94.97   96.40   97.23
summary(stats$overall_rate [-which(stats$genotype =="Lb84" & stats$tissue=="H")])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   95.35   95.79   96.06   96.16   96.64   97.23

Keeping all samples, we have a difference 11% difference between the higher and the lower sample. Without Lb84 heads, the difference is <2%. It is negligible to my opinion.

The analysis have been performed using all the dataset and thats what is presented in the paper. However we also analyzed the dataset excluding the genotype Lb84 for the head. Still, we obtained the same set of candidate genes, excluding any bias due to differences in mapping efficiencies.

3 Define design

# define factors
colData = data.frame(genotype=sample_info$genotype, tissue= sample_info$tissue, infection=sample_info$infection)

dds = DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = countData,
                             colData = colData,
                             design = ~ genotype + 
                               tissue + 
                               infection + 
                               tissue:genotype + 
                               genotype:infection + 
                               tissue:infection)

design(dds)
## ~genotype + tissue + infection + tissue:genotype + genotype:infection + 
##     tissue:infection
# define the reference level for factors:
dds$infection <- relevel(dds$infection, ref = "UI")

5 PCA

5.1 on the full dataset

rld <- rlog(dds)
# remove LbFV loci
rld2=rld[-c(1:108),]

data1 <- plotPCA(rld2, intgroup=c("tissue", "genotype","infection"), returnData=TRUE)
percentVar <- round(100 * attr(data1, "percentVar"))

pca1=ggplot(data1, aes(PC1, PC2)) +
  aes(PC1, PC2, color= infection, shape=genotype)  +
  geom_point(size=3) + 
  stat_ellipse(aes(PC1, PC2, group = data1$tissue),type = "norm", col="grey") +
  annotate("text", label = "ABDO", x = -50, y = 35, size = 5, colour = "darkgrey")+
  annotate("text", label = "HEAD", x = 45, y = 45, size = 5, colour = "darkgrey")+
  xlab(paste0("PC1: ",percentVar[1],"% variance")) +
  ylab(paste0("PC2: ",percentVar[2],"% variance")) +
  ggtitle("(A) Abdomen + Head") +scale_color_manual(values = c("green", "red"))

6 Sample to sample distance

6.1 on the full dataset

# remove LbFV loci and calculate distance
sampleDists <- dist(t(assay(normTransform(dds[-c(1:108),]))))  # data normalized by log2(x+1)

sampleDistMatrix <- as.matrix(sampleDists)
rownames(sampleDistMatrix) <- paste(dds$genotype, dds$infection,dds$tissue, sep="-")
colnames(sampleDistMatrix) <- NULL
colors <- colorRampPalette( rev(brewer.pal(9, "Blues")) )(255)
clustering1=pheatmap(sampleDistMatrix,
         clustering_distance_rows=sampleDists,
         clustering_distance_cols=sampleDists,
         col=colors, main = "(A) ABDOMEN+HEAD",
          fontsize_row=2)

6.2 on the abdomen only

dds_subset=dds[-c(1:108), grep("A", colnames(dds))]

         clustering_distance_rows=sampleDists,

# run analysis on the full model and compare likelihood with reduced one without infection:tissue
design(dds_wasp)
## ~genotype + tissue + infection + tissue:genotype + genotype:infection + 
##     tissue:infection
dds_reduced <- DESeq(dds_wasp, test="LRT", reduced=~  genotype + tissue + infection + tissue:genotype + genotype:infection)
## using pre-existing size factors

## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
res_reduced=results(dds_reduced)

7.2 using separate analysis on head and abdomen

I split the dataset in two :abdomen/head. I then test infection effect, accounting for genotype effect. We choose to test the infection factor by the classical Wald test (instead of LRT test). I checked that LRT tests gave almost the same candidate lists.

7.2.1 Subset data

# subset to abdomen / head
countData_A=countData[,grep(pattern = "A", x = colnames(countData))]
countData_H=countData[,grep(pattern = "H", x = colnames(countData))]

Two functions to plot individual genes

# function to extract tpm values for a given locus
get_TPM=function(locus="MSTRG.10"){
  row=t(tpm[row.names(tpm)==locus,])
  tpm_A=row[grep("A", row.names(row)),]
  tpm_H=row[grep("H", row.names(row)),]

  genotype= colData[colData$tissue=="A",]$genotype
  infection= colData[colData$tissue=="A",]$infection
  data_abdo=data.frame(tpm_A, genotype, infection)
  data_head=data.frame(tpm_H, genotype, infection)
  names(data_abdo)[1]="tpm"
  names(data_head)[1]="tpm"
  data_abdo_means=tapply(X = tpm_A , INDEX = list(genotype, infection), FUN = mean, simplify = T)
  data_head_means=tapply(X = tpm_H , INDEX = list(genotype, infection), FUN = mean, simplify = T)
  # order factors
  data_abdo$infection=factor(x = data_abdo$infection, levels=c("UI", "I"))
  data_head$infection=factor(x = data_head$infection, levels=c("UI", "I"))
  res=list(data_abdo, data_head, data_abdo_means, data_head_means)
  return(res)
}
ggplot_function=function(dataset=tpm, gene="MSTRG.10", tissue="A", size=1, size_title=10, size_points=3, legend=TRUE, xlab=FALSE, ylab=FALSE){
  
# extract data for a given locus
data_locus_i=get_TPM(locus = gene)

if (tissue=="A"){
  d=data_locus_i[[1]]
  means=data_locus_i[[3]]
}

if (tissue=="H"){
  d=data_locus_i[[2]]
  means=data_locus_i[[4]]
}

# plot the data
  # plot the data
if (legend==TRUE) {  
  p  = ggplot(data = d , aes(x=infection, y=tpm, fill=genotype)) + scale_fill_manual(values=c("blue", "black", "red","green"), name="")
  }
if (legend==FALSE) {
    p  = ggplot(d , aes(x=infection, y=tpm, fill=genotype)) + scale_fill_manual(values=c("blue", "black", "red","green"))+ theme (legend.position="none")
}
   p  = p  + geom_point(shape=21, size=size_points, position = position_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0))
   p  = p  + geom_segment(aes(x="UI", xend="I", yend=means[1,1], y=means[1,2]), colour="blue", size=size)
    p  = p  + geom_segment(aes(x="UI", xend="I", yend=means[2,1], y=means[2,2]), colour="black", size=size)
   p  = p  + geom_segment(aes(x="UI", xend="I", yend=means[3,1], y=means[3,2]), colour="red", size=size)
   p  = p  + geom_segment(aes(x="UI", xend="I", yend=means[4,1], y=means[4,2]), colour="green", size=size)
   p  =  p  + ggtitle(paste(gene, tissue))

      if (ylab==TRUE & xlab==TRUE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}
   if (ylab==FALSE & xlab==TRUE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title.y=element_blank(), plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}
      if (ylab==TRUE & xlab==FALSE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title.x=element_blank(), plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}
      if (ylab==FALSE & xlab==FALSE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title.x=element_blank(), axis.title.y=element_blank(),  plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}

   p  =  p  + labs(x = "infection", y="TPM")
   
return(p)
   
}

7.2.8 classification of genes found by the interaction approach

The plots were indivudally observed and classified as specifically abdomen-altered or head-altered depending on their profile. We kept genes with consistent trends for all four genotypes and filtered-out the genes showing up-regulation in one tissue and down-regulation in the other. We thus select genes that are specificially altered in one tissue.

interaction_specific_abdomen_down=NULL

# head altered genes
interaction_specific_head_up=c("XLOC_002874", "XLOC_008873")
interaction_specific_head_down=c("XLOC_001423", "XLOC_010609", "XLOC_011280")

7.2.9 Venn graph of the whole sets of candidates

venn( list(ABDO_up=c(candidates_abdo_up_wald, interaction_specific_abdomen_up), HEAD_up=c(candidates_head_up_wald, interaction_specific_head_up), HEAD_down=c(candidates_head_down_wald, interaction_specific_head_down), ABDO_down=c(candidates_abdo_down_wald, interaction_specific_abdomen_down) ))

# remove genes both deregulated in abdomen and head
to_remove=intersect(candidates_abdo_up_wald, candidates_head_up_wald)
candidates_abdo_up_final=c(candidates_abdo_up_wald, interaction_specific_abdomen_up)
candidates_abdo_up_final2=setdiff(x = candidates_abdo_up_final, to_remove)
candidates_head_up_final=c(candidates_head_up_wald, interaction_specific_head_up)
candidates_head_up_final2=setdiff(x = candidates_head_up_final, to_remove)

# write the final candidate lists
write.table(candidates_abdo_up_final2, file = "../output/candidates_abdo_up_final.txt", quote=F, row.names = F, col.names = F)
write.table(c(candidates_abdo_down_wald, interaction_specific_abdomen_down), file = "../output/candidates_abdo_down_final.txt", quote=F, row.names = F, col.names = F)
write.table(candidates_head_up_final2, file = "../output/candidates_head_up_final.txt", quote=F, row.names = F, col.names = F)
write.table(c(candidates_head_down_wald, interaction_specific_head_down), file = "../output/candidates_head_down_final.txt", quote=F, row.names = F, col.names = F)

10 Sample to sample distance for candidate gene sets

10.1 abdo

dds_subset=dds[candidates_abdo, grep("A", colnames(dds))]

rownames(sampleDistMatrixAc) <- paste(dds_subset$genotype, dds_subset$infection, sep="-")
colnames(sampleDistMatrixAc) <- NULL
colors <- colorRampPalette( rev(brewer.pal(9, "Blues")) )(255)
clustering4=pheatmap(sampleDistMatrixAc,
         clustering_distance_rows=sampleDists,
         clustering_distance_cols=sampleDists,
         col=colors, main = "(D) A (candidates)",
          fontsize_row=4)
